cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

The paper proposes an end-to-end model using convolutional neural networks (CNN) to learn effective features from PEC data for non-destructive inspection (NDI) technique for metal materials. This involves both classification and regression tasks on PEC data. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also involves robotics applications, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics).
